Requirements

Before you start, make sure you have the following programs installed:

Java 17 LTS
Download from Oracle JDK 17



Make sure to set JAVA_HOME to the installation folder (instructions below)

1. Run the following code:
$env:JAVA_HOME="C:\path\to\jdk-17"  
(replace everything in "" with the file location of the extracted jdk file.  Ask Brandon for help if needed)

2.  Then run this code:
$env:PATH="$env:JAVA_HOME\bin;$env:PATH"
(this time go inside the jdk folder and ensure your path goes into the bin folder inside)

3. Run this to verify Java version
java -version  (Use this to verify you're using Java 17)


Maven (included with Spring Boot wrapper, so no separate install required)

Git
Download from Git




----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CLONING THE REPOSITORY

1. Run the following code in a new terminal:
git clone https://github.com/HotHANDZ/SquareScale.git

if this doesn't work, go to our SquareScale github on your computer.  Then click the green "<> Code" button and copy the URL inside.

Then replace the above URL with the one copied from the github

2.  This should pull all the files and folders from the github


NOTE:  If this doesn't work, ensure you have git installed and linked in VSCode.  The profile icon at the bottom left should let you then link your github account



----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
MAKING COMMITS TO THE GITHUB

1. run the following code in the terminal (ENSURE YOU ARE IN THE ROOT FOLDER.  I reccomend running a new terminal)
git add .

2. Run this code and add a comment to what you changed
git commit -m "add your changes test inside the quotations"

3. Push the changes by running this code
git push origin main


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHEN STARTING WORK EACH DAY

1. Run this code to pull all the recent commits
git pull origin main


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
RUNNING A LOCAL HOST TEST THROUGH MAVEN SPRING BOOT

1. Ensure you are in the backend folder by running this in a new terminal:
cd backend

2. Run the following codes:
.\mvnw.cmd clean install
.\mvnw.cmd spring-boot:run

3. Open your internet browser and go to this link:
http://localhost:8080/test

